Author: tusneegnug
Title: â—„ğŸ’ â–ºANNâ—„â–ºICOâ–ºğŸ”µğŸ”µSPOTCOINğŸ”µğŸ”µã€Bountyã€‘ğŸ’ âœ…51% DividendğŸ”¥NEOğŸ”¥
Body: Something is definitely not right with this ICO.  They released what they are calling an "audit" (https://medium.com/spotcoin/spotcoin-post-ico-update-c25c38d014ab) but it raises more questions than it answers and the numbers do not make sense.   **Spotcoin stated terms of sale** * Hard cap: $30M * Soft cap: $5M * Tokens max: 99,000,000 * Team/Public ratio: 1/2 * Max to sell: 66,000,000 * ICO Price: $0.50 * Pre-ICO Price: $0.31-$0.40* * Private Placement Price: Unknown * Per investor token buy limit: 1,000,000 SPOT * Private Placement Allocation/Limit: 16,000,000 SPOT * Pre-ICO Allocation/Limit: 2,500,000 SPOT   **Aduit Figures** * Total fund raise: $14,631,594.94 * Public/sold: 65,204,670 (65.86%) * Treasury: 18,810,000 (19.00%) * Team: 11,770,000 (11.89%) * Marketing: 2,022,335 (2.04%) * Total mint: 97,807,005 (98.79%) * Burned: 1,192,995 (1.21%) * Total: 99,000,000 (100.00%)   This gives an average sale price of just 22.44 cents per token, much lower than any published sale price to date.   If all 16,000,000 private placement tokens were sold for *just 1 cent each*, and all 2,500,000 Pre-ICO tokens were sold at the minimum of 0.31 cents, this would mean the public sale would have an average sale price of just 29.33 cents per token which is below the minimum Pre-ICO price.   Hypothetical sale numbers based on audit: Total    65,204,670      $14,631,594.94          $0.2244 Public   46,704,670      $13,696,594.94          $0.2933 Pre-ICO  2,500,000       $775,000.00             $0.3100 Private  16,000,000      $160,000.00             $0.0100   Something does not seem right...   **Sources** * Spotcoin FAQ - https://spotcoin.com/faq https://archive.fo/UGbk4 * Spotcoin Whitepaper v1.6 October 15 2018 - https://spotcoin.com/whitepaper.pdf https://archive.fo/xJhxX * Spotcoin Steemit - https://steemit.com/neo/@spotcoin/time-to-take-action-exclusive-spot-pre-ico-sale-opens-tuesday https://archive.fo/HRaAx * Spotcoin Medium - https://medium.com/spotcoin/spotcoin-post-ico-update-c25c38d014ab https://archive.fo/4uZLr   *Remember reading somewhere that the Pre-ICO was actually 0.31-0.40 rather than just 0.40 but I cannot find the source, maybe it has been scrubbed?  This is also being discussed on reddit now:  https://www.reddit.com/r/CryptoCurrency/comments/a62y4c/spotcoin_preparing_for_exit_scam/ https://www.reddit.com/r/NEO/comments/a6312m/spotcoin_preparing_to_exit_scam/

Author: cryptohype
Title: â—„ğŸ’ â–ºANNâ—„â–ºICOâ–ºğŸ”µğŸ”µSPOTCOINğŸ”µğŸ”µã€Bountyã€‘ğŸ’ âœ…51% DividendğŸ”¥NEOğŸ”¥
Body: Spotcoin is different from other exchanges in a number of ways.   1) Black Sea region first mover advantage There are no other fiat to digital currency providers in the Black Sea region that can provide access to local national currencies. Spotcoin will unlock the market, giving millions of people easy access to digital currencies for the first time. Spotcoin has been an established OTC in the area since 2016, but only for larger investors who are spending at least $25,000 USD in a single transaction.  Our automated Spotcoin exchange will make it possible for a mass market to buy digital currencies and tokens. This is especially relevant for this region, which is very advanced in its adoption of blockchain technology, and the subject of digital currencies gets plenty of attention among the public. An abundance of cheap electricity makes the region one of the largest providers of currency mining, and there is a great deal of interest among younger people to work in the field. This is a large market waiting for an exchange providing easy fiat to currency access, and Spotcoin will be the first to offer it.  2) Simple liquidity for the NEO We believe wholeheartedly in NEO. NEO is among the most future-proof blockchains because of its current 10,000 TPS capability, and its plans to scale to 100,000 TPS by 2020. However, NEO does at times feel constraints through a lack of direct, simple liquidity. There is little direct free flow of fiat currency to NEO and other NEP-5 based tokens, and Spotcoin will be one of the first to solve that issue. We will provide an easy to use, intuitive interface for the safe trading of not just NEO, but of all NEP-5 standard based tokens that adhere to City of Zion principles, which will be listed on Spotcoin for free. At this time, no other exchange out there offers the same service, and it will provide relief for NEO and all NEO-based companies out there.  3) Highest token dividend Our SPOT token is a dividend token. Unlike some other exchanges, we havenâ€™t tried to force our token into our exchange process as a redundant way to create a use and demand for it. Weâ€™re keeping the business clean and simple. Just like our offer: SPOT token holders will receive 51% of all of the exchange fees from our automated exchange. Every week. To our knowledge, no other exchange offers a dividend this high.  4) Dividends from more than just the exchange Our Spotcoin exchange will not be the only source of revenue, or of dividends. You will receive a 12% dividend from the net profits of our other business lines, quarterly. Like we said, Spotcoin is already an established OTC. We processed over 10 million USD in 2017. We also partner in a 1.1MW Mining Operation, benefitting from Georgiaâ€™s cheap and abundant hydropower.  We have partnered with mining experts Golden Fleece, and aim to expand our joint operations. We have plans to develop SpotPay, a retail application that provides flexible payments using digital currencies to both retailer and consumer. Furthermore, we are an important part of the Black Sea Blockchain Institute, a business incubator and educator in Georgia. As we grow, so will the dividends.   5) More than one leg to stand on Rather than having one pillar for our business, we have several, creating synergies and risk mitigation. Our OTC, our mining operation, our future automated exchange, and retail payment application all provide streams of digital and fiat currencies. At the heart of our system sits our proprietary Spotcore engine, that constantly finds our optimal liquidity. Together, our business lines provide much more stability and security than any single business can. And all SPOT token holders will benefit from them, every week and again every quarter.

Body: To embrace blockchain is to embrace startups  Post from the Official Spotcoin Blog: https://medium.com/spotcoin/to-embrace-blockchain-is-to-embrace-startups-efa3896d69b3   Mariam Lashkhi (left) and Deputy Chairman Avtandil Kasradze of Georgiaâ€™s Innovation and Technology Agency with Nikoloz Khundzakishvili, CORA Director for Efes Brewery (photo: 2018 Black Sea Blockchain Summit)  Angel investors, seed financing, and business incubators play a critical role in advancing blockchain throughout Georgia, many speakers argued on Wednesday at the Black Sea Blockchain Summit.  Speaking of his role in the formation of a business accelerator in the country, Nikoloz Khundzakishvili spoke of his long-term goal to transform Georgia into a startup nation. â€œWe have resources that are everywhere,â€ said Khundzakishvili, CORA Director at Efes Brewery in Georgia.  â€œAccelerators pretty much didnâ€™t exist in Georgia at all ten years ago,â€ said Andrew Thornhill, co-founder of digital currency exchange Spotcoin. â€œGenerally speaking, incubation provides capital and mentorship, and that works,â€ he said.  It is why Spotcoin is using a significant portion of funds raised in its upcoming ICO to fund a new academic facility in the region. The Black Sea Blockchain Institute will teach software developers and business executives, and provide resources for start-ups and scale-ups in the region.  â€œGiving money without structure is losing money. Itâ€™s just throwing it away,â€ Thornhill said.  Khundzakishvili noted that it there is an economic shift underway, where there is more emphasis on selling technology and taking leadership in this latest industrial revolution instead of selling labor. It is a main reason why investment in business incubators is so important.  Blockchain start-ups can also solve governmental issues related to public safety and data security, said Avtandil Kasradze, the Deputy Chairman of Georgiaâ€™s Innovation and Technology Agency. These ambitious businesses are also creating opportunities by furthering new approaches to healthcare, medicine, and the environment.  â€œOpportunities are here. Resources are here. Letâ€™s open the channel to Silicon Valley,â€ Khundzakishvili said.  Digital currency exchange Spotcoin organized the affair, the first major blockchain conference in the country. Around 200 people attended the event, held at Tbilisiâ€™s unique pop-up concept Fabrika.  Interested in Spotcoin or SPOT? Body: Top ICObench advisor Simon Cocking joins Spotcoin   Simon Cocking  Spotcoin is proud to announce that Simon Cocking is an official member of its advisory board. An expert on marketing, media, PR and digital currency strategy, Cocking has advised several ICO launches which achieved their financial targets. Simon Cocking is also Senior Editor at Irish Tech News, Editor in Chief at CryptoCoinNews, and freelances for other publications. He is currently ranked number 1 on People of Blockchain, and he holds the top spot among all ICObench advisors. Spotcoin is an established OTC based in Tblisi, Georgia and will have its initial coin offering (ICO) on May 1st.  â€œI have been educating people about blockchain and its opportunities around the world,â€ Cocking said. â€œSpotcoinâ€™s mission to make digital currencies work for everyone resonates with me. Of course, I had a look at how Spotcoin plans to do this, and I am happy to join and contribute.â€  â€œSimon is one of those special finds: a true expert who as a tech journalist has a real understanding of not just the potential of the technology, but also gets how it works and is able to easily explain it to others,â€ said Spotcoin CEO Tim Gick. He has gained his large following by staying true to his journalistic beliefs and steering clear of paid endorsements. His top ranking on ICObench shows both his knowledge and his integrity. Weâ€™re delighted he agreed to join Spotcoin, as we know he rejects ICOs and projects he doesnâ€™t believe in.â€  In the run-up to the May 1 ICO, Spotcoin has grown its team from a lean, profitable OTC to a much larger enterprise that looks to provide a seamless user experience that simply bridges the gap between legacy currencies and digital assets. Its SPOT token offers 51% of Spotcoin exchange fees as a weekly dividend, and 12% of net profits as a quarterly dividend. The private sale opened on April 10th, withh both public and private sales closing on June 1st.  Residents and citizens of China, South Korea and the United States are prohibited from taking part in the SPOT private and public sales, except accredited U.S. investors, who may take part in the SPOT private sale. Spotcoinâ€™s ICO on May 1st will fund the development of a global, digital exchange platform, the Spotpay retail application and grow its sustainable mining operation. Body: Private Placement KYC white listing is operational on the website.  Create an account at Spotcoin.com  Go to Private Placement on your dashboard and click "Join us"  Ensure you meet the requirements for Private Placement  Click "Continue to KYC" and fill out the form + upload your supporting documents  If you pass the compliance checks, you will receive and email from the Private Placement department to complete the Simple Agreement for Future Tokens (SAFT) agreement

Title: â—„ğŸ’ â–ºANNâ—„â–ºICOâ–ºğŸ”µğŸ”µSPOTCOINğŸ”µğŸ”µã€Bountyã€‘ğŸ’ âœ…51% DividendğŸ”¥NEOğŸ”¥
Body: Good question! Let me list out some reasons:  1. The NEO council is big on compliance with regulators. We are as well! We have been working the Georgian government to be the first licencesed digital exchange in Georgia and continue to build our relationships for further regulation. 2. We believe in a "smart economy" where trustless parties can conduct business through a trusted medium (our business). 3. We are geographically positioned to close the gap between Asia and Western Europe. 4. There is a barrier to purchase 490-500 GAS to create a smart contract on the NEO platform, but it also prevents the scam ICO's from entering the network. 5. We have a good relationship with CoZ and are contributing to the system. 6. ETH has too many issues going on between the forks, PoS debates and Bitmain E3 miner. 7. We plan to contribute to the NEO network by providing nodes to expand their network and allow for a more decentralized system. 8. NEO has plans to integrate KYC, quantum resistance and has multi-language support

Body: So at first when I stumbled upon this ICO I was like: "meh, this service is already provided. not interested".  But after I started reading about them I found out that they provide a lot more: educate the public, fast fiat -> crypto transactions and the willing to bring this whole universe closer to the institutional parts of the countries. By doing this the team and the whole project really contributes a lot to the adoption of this technology.  The inauguration of the Black Sea Blockchain Institute makes me really excited. I think that more than products, new technologies, at this very moment, the people need to be educated about what blockchain does and means. A lot of platforms, apps and Dapps are already there. We just need a voice to direct the people towards this universe that is slowly, but surely emerging. This team is exactly that voice that we all needed. They are continuing what Andreas Antonopoluos (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andreas_Antonopoulos) started long ago.  I really respect a lot this initiative and the whole project.  The project already got a great rating on Icobench: https://icobench.com/ico/spotcoin  Wish you all the best!

Body: TL;DR: You can click on the Why NEO portion https://prezi.com/view/qDNXLoRYKXQe4w1g4r3b/  NEO vs ETH: TPS: 1000 vs 15. NEO can also achieve 10,000 TPS with optimization. We also aim to help NEO achieve the 2020 10,000 TPS goal. Our blockchain institute + accelerator enables us to find talent. Fees: 0 vs $3 avg (Depending on the network) KYC/AML: Yes vs No Fork + Quantum Resistance: Yes vs No Location: Spotcoin is centered between China and Europe, we have a strategic positioning Strategic Alignments: NEO and Spotcoin seek regulation and to expand the digital economy. We also employing a developer to work with CoZ and are offering Node support. Entry Requirement: NEO costs 500 GAS+ vs ETH is virtually free. To us, free isn't necessarily better. It just means an over saturation of s**t coins. We are here to do business. Multi-Language: NEO has multi-language support while ETH requires users to learn solidity

Body: Thanks! We've spent countless hours on which platform made the most business sense. It wasn't cheap since we needed 500 GAS to start the token, but a small investment for a bigger gain. When the NEP-5 tokens receive USD/EUR trading pairs, those markets will do very well. We want to decouple NEO and GAS from BTC in the future. GAS will also become the future of trading since it's divisible and made for trading while NEO is meant for voting rights (hence the non-divisible portion).

Body: Having a payments system enables merchants to trade their cryptocurrency with clients on the exchange and OTC. Clients on the exchange and OTC will pay fiat for the cryptocurrencies. For now, the merchants usually have an overhead that requires fiat. The payments system also enables us to tap into multiple systems that enable Spotcoin to have liquidity.  You can see the process map if you click the "Spotcoin" logo and click on "Payments" https://prezi.com/view/0F9AGHzO9cMqKHVgVLAi/
